=============================\
PART 5 \'97 KMM DOMAIN ADAPTATION\
=============================\
\
Goal:\
Adapt from Java (source domain) to Papua (target domain).\
\
Steps:\
\
1. Extract training samples from:\
   - Source domain: region == "java"\
   - Target domain: region == "papua"\
\
2. Implement Kernel Mean Matching (KMM):\
\
- Use RBF kernel\
- Solve quadratic programming problem:\
    minimize || (1/n_s) \uc0\u931  \u946 _i \u966 (x_i) - (1/n_t) \u931  \u966 (z_j) ||\'b2\
- Constrain:\
    0 <= \uc0\u946 _i <= B\
    | (1/n_s) \uc0\u931  \u946 _i - 1 | <= \u949 \
\
Use cvxopt or a simplified sklearn-compatible solver.\
\
3. Compute weights for Java training samples.\
\
4. Train Transformer again:\
   - Use weighted MSE loss:\
       loss = mean( \uc0\u946 _i * (prediction - target)^2 )\
\
5. Evaluate on Papua test set.\
\
Print:\
- Vanilla Transformer Papua MAE\
- KMM Transformer Papua MAE\
- Improvement %\
